# EmailJS configuration for the Contact form.
# 1. Create a free account at https://www.emailjs.com and add an Email Service.
# 2. Create TWO templates (each with To Email = {{email}}):
#
#    a) NOTIFICATION (arrives in your inbox) -> VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID
#       Content example:
#         Name: {{from_name}}
#         Email: {{from_email}}
#         Message: {{message}}
#
#    b) AUTO-REPLY (thank-you sent to the visitor) -> VITE_EMAILJS_AUTOREPLY_TEMPLATE_ID
#       Content example:
#         Hi {{name}}, thanks for reaching out — I'll get back to you soon.
#
# 3. Copy the IDs/key below, then rename this file to ".env.local".
#    The auto-reply template is optional; without it, only the notification is sent.
#    Without any keys, the form falls back to opening the visitor's mail client.

VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your_service_id
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=your_notification_template_id
VITE_EMAILJS_AUTOREPLY_TEMPLATE_ID=your_autoreply_template_id
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key
